<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-60-0389 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Tapered Bearing Simulator (TBS) has been routinely employed to measurethe high temperature high shear-rate viscosity of non-Newtonian oils.User demands for an increased number of analyses per day and unattendedoperation has encouraged the manufacturer to automate the basic viscometer.This paper addresses the technical development of the automated TBS andincludes a thorough discussion of continuous operation, automatic sampleinjection, and data analysis.</TEXT></DOC>